HEADWORD: Trochil
<hw>Tro"chil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>trochile</ets>. See <er>Trochilus</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>The crocodile bird.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The crocodile . . . opens his chaps to let the <qex>trochil</qex>
in to pick his teeth, which gives it the usual feeding.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
T. Herbert.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

